definitions: not established, decided, or settled with certainty or finality
examples: The cause of the accident remains undetermined pending investigation
They had an undetermined number of guests coming to dinner

definitions: not discouraged or prevented from doing something despite difficulties or opposition
examples: She remained undeterred by the negative feedback on her proposal
The climbers were undeterred by the dangerous weather conditions

definitions: not having reached full growth or maturity in physical or mental aspects
not having buildings, industry, or infrastructure constructed on land or area
examples: The doctor noted the child's undeveloped motor skills needed therapy
His undeveloped ideas required more research before presentation
The company purchased undeveloped land for their new headquarters
Many undeveloped nations struggle with basic infrastructure needs

definitions: not identified or determined through medical examination or professional assessment
examples: Many patients suffer from undiagnosed conditions for years before treatment
Her undiagnosed learning disability affected her school performance significantly

definitions: not having distinct or specialized characteristics that distinguish from others in category
examples: The undifferentiated cells could develop into various tissue types
Their undifferentiated product line failed to stand out in market

definitions: not guided, controlled, or aimed toward a specific goal or purpose
examples: His undirected energy led to many unfinished projects and goals
The undirected discussion wandered through various unrelated topics aimlessly

definitions: lacking self-control, orderly conduct, or systematic training in behavior or performance
examples: The undisciplined students disrupted class with their constant talking
His undisciplined approach to spending created serious financial problems

definitions: not made known or revealed to others, kept secret or confidential
examples: The company sold for an undisclosed amount to private investors
She had undisclosed reasons for suddenly leaving her job position

definitions: not yet found, detected, or known about by people or science
examples: Scientists believe many undiscovered species exist in ocean depths
The artist remained undiscovered until after her death years later

definitions: not questioned, challenged, or doubted as being true or legitimate by anyone
examples: She was the undisputed champion after winning five consecutive tournaments
The undisputed facts of the case led to quick verdict

definitions: lacking distinction, excellence, or notable qualities that set apart from ordinary
examples: His undistinguished career ended without any major achievements or recognition
The building's undistinguished architecture blended into the surrounding structures

definitions: not interrupted, interfered with, or bothered by external influences or people
examples: The artifacts remained undisturbed in the tomb for thousands years
She needed undisturbed time to focus on her important project

definitions: not separated or broken into parts, remaining whole and intact
concentrated wholly on one object without being shared or distracted
examples: The property remained undivided among the family members for generations
The undivided highway stretched for miles through the desert landscape
Please give me your undivided attention during this safety briefing
She devoted her undivided energy to completing the research project

definitions: lacking proper legal documents, especially regarding immigration or work status
not recorded in writing or other permanent form for reference
examples: Many undocumented workers face challenges accessing healthcare and education services
The undocumented immigrants sought legal assistance for their status
The software had many undocumented features users discovered by accident
Their undocumented agreement later caused disputes about the terms

definitions: not finished or completed, left in an incomplete state
not fastened, tied, or secured properly, having come loose
examples: Several tasks remained undone at the end of the workday
Her undone homework resulted in a lower grade than expected
His shirt came undone during the vigorous dance performance
The package came undone in transit, spilling its contents

definitions: not wearing clothes or having removed one's clothing
not prepared, treated, or finished properly for use or presentation
examples: He felt undressed without his usual business suit and tie
The patient was undressed for the medical examination by staff
The undressed wound needed immediate cleaning and proper bandaging
The undressed salad lacked any dressing or seasoning for flavor

definitions: exceeding what is appropriate, normal, or necessary in degree or amount
examples: The court found undue influence in the elderly woman's will
Don't put undue pressure on yourself to be absolutely perfect

definitions: lasting forever or indefinitely, especially regarding feelings or devotion
examples: He declared his undying love for her in the letter
The soldiers showed undying loyalty to their country and cause

definitions: not gained or deserved through one's own effort, work, or merit
examples: Critics said his promotion was unearned and based on favoritism
The trust fund provided unearned income for life without working

definitions: seeming not to belong to this world, supernatural or mysteriously strange
occurring at an extremely early or late hour considered unreasonable
examples: An unearthly glow emanated from the abandoned house at night
The unearthly beauty of the aurora borealis amazed the viewers
She called at an unearthly hour, waking the entire household
Getting up at unearthly times for work affected his health

definitions: feeling worried, anxious, or uncomfortable about something uncertain or potentially problematic
examples: She felt uneasy about walking alone in the unfamiliar neighborhood
An uneasy silence filled the room after the argument ended

definitions: not profitable or efficient in terms of money, resources, or practical value
examples: The factory closure was due to uneconomic production costs rising
Running empty buses on that route proved uneconomic for company

definitions: not revised, corrected, or prepared for publication through editing process
examples: The unedited manuscript contained numerous spelling and grammar errors throughout
She posted the unedited photos directly from her camera online

definitions: having little or no formal education or academic instruction and knowledge
examples: Despite being uneducated, he built a successful business through experience
The uneducated guess turned out to be surprisingly accurate nonetheless

definitions: not having paid work but available and actively seeking employment
examples: The unemployed workers gathered to protest for more job opportunities
She remained unemployed for six months before finding suitable position

definitions: not burdened, restricted, or slowed down by obligations, debts, or obstacles
examples: He enjoyed the unencumbered lifestyle of a bachelor without responsibilities
The unencumbered property had no liens or mortgages against it

definitions: having or seeming to have no end, continuing indefinitely without stopping
examples: The unending rain caused severe flooding throughout the entire region
She faced an unending stream of emails in her inbox

definitions: not able to be enforced or made effective through legal or official means
examples: The contract contained several unenforceable clauses according to state law
Without proper documentation, the agreement was legally unenforceable in court

definitions: not showing or feeling excitement, interest, or eagerness about something
examples: The audience gave an unenthusiastic response to the presentation
His unenthusiastic attitude toward the project concerned his manager

definitions: not equal in quantity, size, quality, or value between things
not providing the same rights, opportunities, or treatment to different people
examples: The unequal lengths of rope made the swing hang crooked
They divided the inheritance into unequal portions among siblings
The unequal pay for same work sparked protests among employees
Society struggles with unequal access to quality education and healthcare

definitions: leaving no doubt, absolutely clear and unambiguous in meaning or intent
examples: The CEO gave an unequivocal statement denying all merger rumors
The test results provided unequivocal proof of the substance's toxicity

definitions: not conforming to accepted standards of moral or professional conduct
examples: The unethical business practices led to heavy fines and lawsuits
Sharing confidential patient information would be unethical and illegal

definitions: not level, flat, or smooth, having an irregular surface
not regular, consistent, or equal in quality, treatment, or distribution
examples: The uneven pavement caused several people to trip and fall
She applied makeup to cover the uneven skin tone
His uneven performance throughout the season disappointed fans and coaches
The uneven distribution of resources created conflict among departments

definitions: not marked by interesting or exciting events, routine and ordinary
examples: After yesterday's drama, today was pleasantly uneventful and calm
The uneventful flight arrived at its destination right on schedule

definitions: not having reached the end of validity period, still current
examples: She renewed her unexpired passport to avoid future travel delays
The store accepted returns only with unexpired receipts from purchase

definitions: not explained or accounted for, having no known reason or cause
examples: The unexplained noise in the attic kept them awake all night
Several unexplained absences from work led to her eventual termination

definitions: not having exploded or detonated but still capable of doing so
examples: The bomb squad carefully removed the unexploded ordnance from site
Workers discovered unexploded shells from the war during construction excavation

definitions: not yet investigated, examined, or traveled through to gain knowledge
examples: The unexplored cave system attracted adventurous spelunkers from worldwide
Many unexplored career options existed beyond her current field

definitions: not loyal or true to a partner in a romantic relationship
not true to facts, original, or source material in representation
examples: His unfaithful behavior destroyed their marriage of twenty years
She couldn't forgive her unfaithful partner despite his apologies
The movie was unfaithful to the book's original plot and characters
The unfaithful translation lost much of the poem's original meaning

definitions: not known or recognized from previous experience or knowledge
examples: The unfamiliar surroundings made her feel anxious and lost
He struggled with the unfamiliar technical terms in the manual

definitions: not conforming to current fashion, style trends, or popular taste
examples: His unfashionable clothes made him stand out at the party
The once-trendy neighborhood became unfashionable and property values dropped

definitions: not giving advantage or expressing disapproval, negative in effect or opinion
examples: The unfavorable weather conditions forced them to cancel the event
Critics gave unfavorable reviews to the highly anticipated movie premiere

definitions: not possible to do or carry out practically given current circumstances
examples: The ambitious timeline proved unfeasible given their limited resources available
Building a bridge there was unfeasible due to environmental regulations

definitions: not confined, restricted, or controlled by rules, obligations, or restraints
examples: The artist enjoyed unfettered creative freedom in her new studio
Unfettered access to information helped researchers make breakthrough discoveries

definitions: not filled, occupied, or supplied with what is needed or expected
examples: Several unfilled positions remained open due to skill shortages
The unfilled orders accumulated as production fell behind schedule

definitions: not completed or brought to an end, lacking final details
examples: The unfinished painting revealed the artist's creative process clearly
She left many unfinished projects when she moved away suddenly

definitions: not suitable or appropriate for a particular purpose or role
not in good physical condition or health for activity
examples: The contaminated water was unfit for human consumption or use
His aggressive behavior made him unfit for leadership position
Years of inactivity left him unfit and struggling with stairs
The doctor declared her temporarily unfit for work after surgery

definitions: not showing someone or something in an attractive or favorable way
examples: The unflattering photo caught her in an awkward facial expression
His unflattering comments about colleagues damaged his professional reputation

definitions: not showing fear or hesitation in facing difficulty, danger, or pain
examples: Her unflinching courage during the crisis inspired everyone around her
The documentary took an unflinching look at poverty and injustice

definitions: lacking clear purpose, concentration, or sharp definition in thought or vision
examples: His unfocused approach to studying resulted in poor test scores
The unfocused photograph looked blurry and indistinct to viewers
